Citation.sTitle: Solubilities of Terephthalic Acid in Dimethyl Sulfoxide + Water and in N,N-Dimethylformamide + Water from (301.4 to 373.7) K
Citation.sAbstract: By use of the static analytical method, the solubilities of terephthalic acid in binary dimethyl sulfoxide (2) + water and in binary N,N-dimethylformamide (2) + water solvent mixtures were determined in the temperature range from (301.4 to 373.7) K and solvent composition range from (w2 = 0.8 to 1.0). The solubility data were correlated with an empirical equation.

CompositionAtPhaseEquilibrium.sMethodName: titration with standard sodium hydroxide solution using phenolphthalein as indicator
